Description: Fragment of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Neck and oval handle to sharp turn. Rectangular stamp with caduceus symbol. Clay fine pink-brown; cream slip.
Curator's comments: Drawn by Petrie (Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 206, 15). Name Ermaios. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0283.16?
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1187)
